Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.76,0:00:04.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A threatening letter from the Guardian of Time.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.60,0:00:08.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The letter warned that the mistress of a\Nclock mansion, Hoshina Rukako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.93,0:00:12.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was to be murdered during her birthday party.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.36,0:00:18.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We were invited to the party, along with Uncle,\Nwho had taken up the job of her bodyguard.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.08,0:00:25.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Still, as the chime indicating 6:00 PM sounded,\Nshe was murdered by a person unknown.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.00,0:00:32.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit used a sharp weapon akin to an\Nice pick to stab Rukako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} in the heart...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.86,0:00:34.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then apparently fled from the balcony.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.55,0:00:38.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the baffling part was, on the ground wet from the rain...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.60,0:00:41.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There wasn't even a single footprint left by the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.73,0:00:45.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Four years ago, during the birthday party at Hoshina Manor...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.40,0:00:47.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone also lost their life.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.28,0:00:51.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A clock technician fell as he was repairing the great clock...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.36,0:00:54.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The search was delayed because of the party, and he died.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.70,0:00:59.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran trembled at the thought of the Guardian of Time\Nbeing the ghost of the clock technician, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.62,0:01:01.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, that's not it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.54,0:01:05.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I shall definitely unravel their true identity!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.43,0:01:11.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like fog clearing up in a swoosh...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.15,0:01:12.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's see through both romance and cases!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.90,0:01:15.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The real culprit that reigns over time...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.11,0:01:17.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's solve the mystery of the invisible murder weapon!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.22,0:01:18.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.80,0:01:20.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The appearance of a chi d and the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.77,0:01:22.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.54,0:03:13.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you're the architect...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.71,0:03:15.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The name's Karube.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.03,0:03:16.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I designed this mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.38,0:03:21.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You have blood on your hands and your shirt cuffs.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.80,0:03:25.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It must have gotten there when I rushed to\Nthe mistress's side when she collapsed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.26,0:03:29.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But there's no blood on me other than that, is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.93,0:03:30.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.10,0:03:35.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, did you notice anything at the time of the crime?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.56,0:03:42.08,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Karube Teigo (45)\NArchitect
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.57,0:03:41.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, I think I heard a sound\Nlike cloth rubbing together approaching us.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.07,0:03:44.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe the culprit was a woman in a dress?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.57,0:03:48.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, the tip of that pipe of yours...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.79,0:03:53.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks long and sharp to me, so would you allow us to examine it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.46,0:03:57.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold on, you're way out of line!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.38,0:04:01.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While it's true the clock technician who\Ndied four years ago was my brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.63,0:04:04.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that I'm likely to have the strongest motive...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.64,0:04:06.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that was just an unfortunate accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.05,0:04:09.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I held no grudge against the mistress!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.94,0:04:11.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.43,0:04:14.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were in charge of the mansion's interior design, Suou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.65,0:04:17.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As such, you could have set up any number of tricks.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.86,0:04:23.82,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The same could be said of Karube{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} the architect\Nand Furugaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} who constructed that great clock!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.19,0:04:24.16,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Suou Chiaki (39)\NInterior Designer
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.49,0:04:27.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But probably not Furugaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who's getting on in years.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.91,0:04:29.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How come?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.45,0:04:37.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After the culprit stabbed the mistress, they moved\Nquite nimbly and brushed up against my left side!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.42,0:04:41.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So here, you can see traces of blood having\Nrubbed off on my left arm, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.42,0:04:45.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, what's that you have stuck in your hair?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.64,0:04:49.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An ornate hairpin my brother bought me a while ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.22,0:04:52.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would you mind if we examined it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.85,0:04:54.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Check it to your heart's content!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.69,0:05:00.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not like those in historical dramas.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.69,0:05:02.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no blade inside!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.74,0:05:05.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.99,0:05:07.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was you, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.70,0:05:11.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The clock craftsman who constructed that great clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.16,0:05:13.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I'm Furugaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.04,0:05:16.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems that you have a little blood\Nthat flew onto your right shoulder.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.17,0:05:22.55,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Furugaki Rinsaku (64)\NClock Technician
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.46,0:05:22.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess it was because that woman was stabbed to the right of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.34,0:05:27.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And for your information, I think the\Nculprit was a pretty plump fellow.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.05,0:05:33.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was pushed right before that woman let out a scream.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.22,0:05:36.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By a soft, springy body.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.69,0:05:41.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true that I weigh 78 kilograms and am slightly overweight, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.32,0:05:45.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Does that have any bearing on the case?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.57,0:05:48.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it's just for our records.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.49,0:05:52.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, Oume{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.24,0:05:54.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Regarding this knife found next to the cake...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.79,0:05:58.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We found your fingerprints on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.58,0:06:04.21,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Oume Gakumichi (42)\NHoshina Family Butler
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.88,0:06:00.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course you did!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.59,0:06:04.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was my duty as butler to cut the cake after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.42,0:06:05.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.34,0:06:09.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After the flames from the candles were out\Nyou didn't turn the lights back on immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.09,0:06:09.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How come?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.64,0:06:12.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because the mistress didn't give me the signal.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.02,0:06:18.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Usually, right after they're blown out,\Nthe clocks would chime for 6:00 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.81,0:06:24.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And after they finished chiming, the mistress would\Nsnap her fingers as a cue to turn back on the lights.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.73,0:06:29.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But at that time, the clocks didn't chime immediately, did they?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.74,0:06:30.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.07,0:06:37.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the three clock technicians monitoring the clocks that\Nwere supposedly behind said they all chimed on time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.37,0:06:39.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Apart from that...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.94,0:06:44.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though you were right by the mistress's side, you\Ndon't have even one drop of blood splatter on you!?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.38,0:06:47.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that because the culprit had a large build?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.26,0:06:51.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why the blood splatter didn't reach me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.85,0:06:59.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone in a dress who moved nimbly,\Nyet is plump and of a large build...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.10,0:07:03.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was there such a person among the guests?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.40,0:07:04.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.48,0:07:09.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We checked all of the 65 guests who came to the party,\Nbut there wasn't anyone matching that description.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.65,0:07:13.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, there were no guests possessing anything\Nresembling a weapon, is that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.70,0:07:14.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.95,0:07:19.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I was told there was no luminol\Nreaction on the belongings of those four.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.88,0:07:22.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In short, like that threatening letter said...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.55,0:07:26.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The murder might as well have been carried\Nout using a "formless sword," then?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.84,0:07:27.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It sure seems that way...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.38,0:07:32.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.26,0:07:36.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About the blood on the handrail and window\Nframe, was it all from the mistress?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.31,0:07:36.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.56,0:07:41.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know how they were able to obtain the\Nmistress's blood before the crime, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.89,0:07:44.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If they wanted to make it look like they fled through the window...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.69,0:07:47.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They would've had to plant the blood beforehand.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.07,0:07:49.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, isn't that strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.74,0:07:53.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If they're making it look like they fled from here...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.32,0:07:59.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rather than making these rubbed-of blood marks, it would've\Nbeen more convincing if they had left clear, bloody footprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.83,0:08:01.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who knows?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.44,0:08:07.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe they thought if the marks were too clear, the jig\Nwould have been up before the crime even started?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.71,0:08:09.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.76,0:08:11.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Midnight already?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.22,0:08:14.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, so this room was directly below that great clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.39,0:08:21.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, that's not it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.68,0:08:23.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These blood marks weren't made beforehand!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.06,0:08:27.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That "Guardian of Time" really passed through here...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.90,0:08:29.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the time of the crime...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.61,0:08:30.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And all according to plan!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.45,0:08:36.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The results from everyone's body search...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.41,0:08:39.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Showed that no one had hidden a weapon on their person.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.66,0:08:44.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In addition, it seems no one had been covered\Nin a large amount of blood splatter, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.21,0:08:49.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll wrap things up for today, and conduct\Nmore thorough interviews at a later date.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.63,0:08:53.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.67,0:08:56.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No objections, right, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.05,0:08:56.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.64,0:09:00.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems instead of the mystery of the missing weapon...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.43,0:09:05.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we consider the fleeing from this balcony without\Nleaving any footprints behind as some sort of trick...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.94,0:09:07.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would be for the best.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.02,0:09:10.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad!?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.69,0:09:14.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Round and round I go again...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.40,0:09:17.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Twirl, twirl!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.24,0:09:18.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Watch out!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.46,0:09:19.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh no!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.45,0:09:24.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you think you're doing, geez!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.96,0:09:26.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were about to fall!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.75,0:09:29.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,True.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.04,0:09:30.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was indeed on the verge of falling...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.09,0:09:34.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Into the cunning scheme...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.97,0:09:36.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Set up by the culprit snickering in this very room!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.55,0:09:41.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, the culprit really is someone here?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.60,0:09:43.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now look here, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.98,0:09:47.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although it's intriguing that the culprit's\Nfootprints were absent below the balcony...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.70,0:09:53.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's unthinkable that the culprit could be someone here!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.32,0:09:53.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.69,0:09:56.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Allow me to reconstruct the crime at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.28,0:09:59.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Reconstruct?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.53,0:10:00.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.66,0:10:06.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'll take a short while to prepare, so if the inspector and\Nguests would please leave the room for a few moments.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.05,0:10:15.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just how long do they expect to keep us waiting?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.80,0:10:20.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems the young detective and the butler\Nhave been in and out quite a few times now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.80,0:10:22.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder if they'll really be able to prove it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.10,0:10:27.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How to stab someone without getting blood splatter\Non them, and how to dispose of the weapon...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.98,0:10:31.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez, going so far as to shut even me out of the room...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.02,0:10:34.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He'll really get it if this turns out to be another worthless deduction!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.71,0:10:35.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you for waiting!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.71,0:10:40.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We have finished our preparations, so if\Neveryone would please enter the room!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.62,0:10:43.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.54,0:10:47.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector, please hang this around your neck.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.91,0:10:53.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't this the flashlight watch that Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s always wearing?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.25,0:10:54.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.46,0:10:58.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're having you play the part of the murdered victim...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.59,0:11:01.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Meaning this will take the place of the\Nnecklace covered in fluorescent paint.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.62,0:11:10.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It doesn't seem like much has been changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.44,0:11:11.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.54,0:11:17.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only thing that's different is that boy with\Nglasses standing in front of the closed window.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.36,0:11:25.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know what you're up to, but out with it already.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.79,0:11:27.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.95,0:11:30.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're recreating the scene as it was at the time of the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.54,0:11:35.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First, the lights in the room were turned off\Nand the cake was brought here, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.71,0:11:36.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.13,0:11:38.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.38,0:11:41.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On my cue, please blow out the candles as the victim did.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.37,0:11:45.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Three...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.45,0:11:46.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Two...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.39,0:11:46.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.18,0:11:47.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.73,0:11:53.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who was that!?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.48,0:11:55.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who just hit me in the head with a stick!?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.98,0:12:02.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, what's with this experiment?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.70,0:12:07.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's useless even if you open the window and pretend to have fled!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.37,0:12:09.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since I saw the stick used by whoever hit me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.41,0:12:14.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means the one who still has the\Nstick is definitely the one who hit me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.37,0:12:14.79,Signs,,0,0,0,,Sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.92,0:12:17.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one who hit you, Inspector...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.96,0:12:18.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.67,0:12:21.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't talk nonsense, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.26,0:12:24.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For,starters, you're not even carrying a stick!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.02,0:12:27.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no reason I would be.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.35,0:12:31.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since the stick I hit you with\Nflew away and disappeared out the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.27,0:12:31.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.40,0:12:44.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.03,0:12:46.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That the stick flew over here?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.24,0:12:46.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.44,0:12:50.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, what flew over here wasn't a stick.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.04,0:12:52.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was an umbrella pulled by a string.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.27,0:12:53.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An umbrella?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.42,0:12:55.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, is it true?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.13,0:12:57.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.09,0:12:59.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This umbrella.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.00,0:13:03.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well now, it took quite a while to prepare this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.26,0:13:05.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had to ask the butler for a long string...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.90,0:13:13.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then ask the clockwork technicians to set the great\Nclock ahead so that it read 6:00—the time of the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.43,0:13:14.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The clock?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.90,0:13:17.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's all this about?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.56,0:13:18.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is how the trick worked.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.98,0:13:24.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First, prepare a long string and tie a weight in the middle of it...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.20,0:13:28.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And on one end of the string, install a slippery, ring-like object.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.74,0:13:34.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then attach that ring through the gap in the\Ndecorative tip of the great clock's hour hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.66,0:13:39.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As you dangle the end with the weight so that\Nit goes over the handrail of the balcony.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.34,0:13:45.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next, you pass the other end of the string through\Nthe gap in the window and into the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.09,0:13:49.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait until the room's darkened for\Nblowing out the candles on the cake...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.60,0:13:55.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then tie the string in the room onto the\Numbrella handle to complete the preparations.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.64,0:14:01.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Afterwards, as when Conan hit your head\Nwith the umbrella seconds before 6:00...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.44,0:14:05.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A few seconds later, the great clock's\Nhour hand would face straight down.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.61,0:14:09.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The ring on the string would fall\Nout from the gap in the ornament.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.16,0:14:15.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, the dangling weight would fall as the umbrella\Nwas pulled to force its way out the window...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.37,0:14:17.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it fell from the balcony.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.04,0:14:20.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And thus, its disappearance from the room is complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.58,0:14:22.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now look, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.37,0:14:25.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The weapon and the weight weren't on the ground below.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.84,0:14:30.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And first of all, wouldn't someone have\Nnoticed the presence of the string?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.26,0:14:35.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, let's say the string is a fishing\Nline that's thin and hard to see...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.06,0:14:42.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we inserted the weight in the middle of that line\Ninto the lattice of the well below the great clock...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.11,0:14:43.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't that work?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.52,0:14:44.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.78,0:14:49.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The murder weapon pulled by the\Nweight would be sucked into the well!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.45,0:14:50.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.70,0:14:57.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since the well is scheduled to be filled two weeks later,\Nthe weapon would never again seen the light of day.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.87,0:15:01.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, why wasn't the culprit drenched in the blood splatter?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.01,0:15:03.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That reminds me...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.34,0:15:06.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wasn't there a lot of testimony about the culprit's description?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.88,0:15:12.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That the culprit was of large build,\Nplump, nimble, and a woman in a dress.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.09,0:15:13.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In fact...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.26,0:15:15.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those were all descriptions of the weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.88,0:15:17.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The weapon?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.52,0:15:24.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seemed to be nimble because the blood-soaked weapon\Nflew out the window as a result of the trick just now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.07,0:15:31.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was thought to be of large build because the\Nweapon covers quite a large area when expanded.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.13,0:15:37.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it was said to be plump since you'd feel a springy\Nresistance if you were pushed by the weapon...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.75,0:15:44.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Given that the weapon was covered in cloth, you could\Nhear a rubbing sound resembling the fabric of a dress.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.21,0:15:48.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What on earth is this weapon you're talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.43,0:15:52.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The same thing I hit you with, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.01,0:15:53.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's this!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.85,0:15:55.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An umbrella?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.84,0:16:01.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See, if the culprit attached a sharp weapon\Nwith something like a screw to this tip...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.94,0:16:04.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They could have stabbed the mistress and pulled it out...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.98,0:16:07.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Without getting blood splatter on them, no?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.65,0:16:08.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, Uncle?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.32,0:16:10.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.78,0:16:12.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This happened during the party!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.95,0:16:15.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If someone carried an umbrella in, wouldn't it stand out?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.20,0:16:18.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it could be smuggled in on the culprit's person.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.87,0:16:21.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Karube{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.04,0:16:23.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was your foldable umbrella, to be exact!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.17,0:16:31.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.72,0:16:35.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While using an umbrella as the weapon\Ncould prevent the blood splatter...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.74,0:16:39.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would've been a hassle to fold the umbrella later, wouldn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.18,0:16:41.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.00,0:16:48.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There wasn't enough time to do that between the\Nmistress's scream and the start of the great clock's chime!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.42,0:16:50.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Folding it could have been done instantly.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.15,0:16:55.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just close the umbrella without\Nworrying about blood on your hands...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.45,0:16:58.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And cinch it up with a rubber band or\Nsomething along those lines on your wrist.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.96,0:16:59.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.70,0:17:04.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why both of Karube{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s\Nhands have so much blood on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.67,0:17:05.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.04,0:17:09.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As the last person to close the small\Nwindow on the great clock dial...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.03,0:17:13.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were able to set up the line trick on the hour hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.22,0:17:16.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And by saying you were going to pray at the well afterwards...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.68,0:17:21.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You could've pulled the line lowered to the ground toward\Nthe well, as you tied the weight while pretending to pray.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.56,0:17:26.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next, as the architect who designed this mansion...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.10,0:17:30.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You would've found it easy to estimate how much line you needed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.77,0:17:35.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And by holding the mistress's pocket\Nwatch before your crime, you could...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.57,0:17:42.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Set the time a few seconds ahead, and between the mistress's\Nblowing of the candles and the chime of the great clock...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.24,0:17:44.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were able to use the short interval to commit the crime!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.75,0:17:50.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But wasn't Karube{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} the who said\Nhe heard the rubbing sound of fabric?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.54,0:17:54.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he were the culprit, would he say something\Nso closely linked with an umbrella?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.76,0:17:56.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He purposely said it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.38,0:18:00.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He purposely threw in a true fact in order to mislead us...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.85,0:18:03.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Into thinking the culprit might be a woman in a dress.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.39,0:18:08.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Had he told a complete lie, he'd be the only one\Nto testify differently than the other guests...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.81,0:18:10.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And would've appeared suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.27,0:18:12.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.36,0:18:18.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But didn't Karube{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} stop the guests when they wanted to\Nleave without cooperating with the police investigation?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.41,0:18:22.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saying we should assist the police for the late mistress's sake!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.19,0:18:24.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think he would've just left if he were the culprit!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.48,0:18:26.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.95,0:18:29.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if he had wanted to leave, he couldn't have.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.46,0:18:33.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because the rain suddenly started up again.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.10,0:18:38.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The umbrella he carried when he first came here had\Nbeen used as the weapon, and was then in the well.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.03,0:18:45.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he had just left, the fact that he no longer had\Nthe umbrella he should have would be revealed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.60,0:18:46.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How careless of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.56,0:18:51.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If only you had anticipated such a\Nthing and brought an extra umbrella...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.39,0:18:55.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I did place an extra umbrella into my bag, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.06,0:19:03.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems my wife unfortunately took\Nthe extra umbrella out of my bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.65,0:19:08.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since a note saying, "Isn't one umbrella enough?" was inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.45,0:19:12.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, since it was raining like I'd been waiting for...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.28,0:19:17.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wasn't able to curb my impatience and neglected\Nto double-check, and that was my mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.79,0:19:19.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You say you'd been waiting...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.71,0:19:22.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So ever since two years ago when\Nthe first threatening letter was received...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.92,0:19:25.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'd been planning this murder?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.55,0:19:26.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.34,0:19:31.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it's raining, the lack of footprints from the\Nfleeing culprit can be explained away...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.51,0:19:37.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And since no one will go out to that roofless balcony,\NI wouldn't have to worry about having my trick exposed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.19,0:19:44.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although, when the rain stopped right\Nbefore my crime, I did get a bit nervous.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.02,0:19:47.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, you admit to the crime?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.07,0:19:47.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.36,0:19:54.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since the umbrella that fell into the wall will be covered\Nwith the mistress's blood and with my fingerprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.87,0:19:56.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, why?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.29,0:19:59.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did you kill that woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.58,0:20:07.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because I wanted to avenge my childhood friend,\Nthe clock technician, who died because of her.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.38,0:20:09.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that reason enough?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.64,0:20:13.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, didn't you say it at my brother's funeral?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.80,0:20:16.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That it was an unfortunate accident?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.39,0:20:17.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.43,0:20:20.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I did let myself believe that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.83,0:20:25.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Until I heard that woman's conversation on the day of the funeral.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.32,0:20:28.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold on, what's the meaning of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.65,0:20:32.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How come you still haven't found a replacement clock technician?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.85,0:20:34.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I sincerely apologize...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.04,0:20:39.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whenever I think of the late clock technician,\NI can't bring myself to look for a replacement...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.04,0:20:41.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Haven't I already told you!?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.37,0:20:44.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Broken clocks must be thrown away and replaced with new ones!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.67,0:20:46.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't it the same with clock technicians!?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.92,0:20:49.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How cruel...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.60,0:20:52.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was a man who loved clocks more than anyone...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.27,0:20:56.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you're working here as a clock technician?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.97,0:20:57.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.43,0:21:00.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But are you doing all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.02,0:21:02.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't the mistress here really strict about time?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.94,0:21:04.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's fine, it's fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.02,0:21:07.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That makes it even more worthwhile!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.23,0:21:10.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And since I arrived, not a single clock has had to be thrown out!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.94,0:21:16.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, these clocks here have my spirit\Ninside, and are just like my family!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.34,0:21:18.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're all doing our best!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.96,0:21:22.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Big brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.19,0:21:29.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.71,0:21:32.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Instead of avenging him...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.59,0:21:36.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was more like I wanted to rescue them.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.05,0:21:39.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From the Tyrant of Time...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.28,0:21:40.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His so-called family...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.82,0:23:03.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Clocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.53,0:23:09.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're necessary partners in our daily\Nlives—it's an inseverable relationship.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.08,0:23:11.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, once in a while, they lose time.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.70,0:23:15.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Genta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, you're late!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.46,0:23:16.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.58,0:23:18.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My alarm clock was acting up!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.23,0:23:23.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me you're still using that old clock?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.88,0:23:24.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.80,0:23:27.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since I got it from my late grandma...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.34,0:23:29.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I might get cursed if I throw it away!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.68,0:23:33.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if it's your precious clock, then cut it some slack.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.68,0:23:40.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since clocks don't rest even when we sleep, and\Nwork nonstop with that tick-tock sound...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.82,0:23:44.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Regardless, Edogawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} sure is late.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.82,0:23:51.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we don't leave soon, it'll be night\Nby the time we get to the campsite!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.58,0:23:53.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I bet he's still asleep!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.77,0:23:59.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tick, tock, tick, tock, tick, tock...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.22,0:24:01.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hostess!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.15,0:24:03.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please bring each of us some drinks!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.59,0:24:04.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My, my.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.02,0:24:07.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sir, aren't you a generous one!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.38,0:24:10.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{no hardsub}I think Dad recently frequents this area to get his drink fix.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.90,0:24:14.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To think he's able to drink sake in such a smoky place!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.54,0:24:20.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So this means someone among the customers killed the hostess.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.11,0:24:29.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,THE SUPER NARROW SHOP CRIME SCENE
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.29,0:24:47.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint is...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.75,0:24:49.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Glass
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.14,0:24:51.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Our next story has a Shouwa vibe?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.85,0:24:52.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no screen time for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.85,0:24:54.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This Great Detective will be on a roll!
